    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>it's just... they have so much on their plates already. work, their own families, and then they have to come here and deal with my appointments and my moods and the way I can't even do things for myself anymore. i see it in their eyes. they love me, i know they do, but it's like every time they walk through that door, i'm just one more thing they have to manage. it feels so selfish to keep dragging them into this.",
